reviews.review_text:
Sound Quality = A plus One of the best live AUD recordings I've heard... I now know what I kind of passed over back in the years it was happening: that early Bruce shows from fall 90 all the way to fall 91 are A TREAT!!  I guess the 2 keyboard and Vince hadn't grown on me yet factors obscured what I now hear are just sparking shows!!  Here, the whole sequence from the Terrapin ending jam and into a more than just interesting 'Drums' , and a really awesomely built up and played 'Space' then victorious into an uptempo Wheel, with Jerry rolling the wheel (so-to-speak) non stop, all throughout the song... nice 
and beautiful Stella Blue etc... 
Sound quality is great here... hard to believe there isn't a SBD source matrixed in!  Very clear , all instruments, deep bass, etc.  even nice balance of crowd.  Pin drop during Stella ;-)
